#: ../client/gameCategoryIntro.ts:55
msgid "Game category filter"
msgstr "Játék kategória szűrő "

#: ../client/gameCategoryIntro.ts:56
msgid ""
"Pychess supports more than 60 variants across many chess families, so the "
"lobby, puzzles, tournaments, and menus can feel very broad."
msgstr ""
"Pychess supports more than 60 variants across many chess families, so the "
"lobby, puzzles, tournaments, and menus can feel very broad."

#: ../client/gameCategoryIntro.ts:57
msgid ""
"If you mostly play a regional chess, you can focus the whole site to that "
"family: Shogi (Japanese), Xiangqi/Janggi (Chinese/Korean), or Makruk/Ouk "
"Chaktrang (Thai/Cambodian)."
msgstr ""
"If you mostly play a regional chess, you can focus the whole site to that "
"family: Shogi (Japanese), Xiangqi/Janggi (Chinese/Korean), or Makruk/Ouk "
"Chaktrang (Thai/Cambodian)."

#: ../client/gameCategoryIntro.ts:58
msgid ""
"This trims the variant lists, keeps recommendations and events in your area "
"of interest, and makes the site feel like a dedicated hub rather than a huge"
" catalog. Think of it as creating a lishogi.org-style experience inside "
"Pychess."
msgstr ""
"This trims the variant lists, keeps recommendations and events in your area "
"of interest, and makes the site feel like a dedicated hub rather than a huge"
" catalog. Think of it as creating a lishogi.org-style experience inside "
"Pychess."

#: ../client/gameCategoryIntro.ts:59
msgid ""
"You can switch anytime in Preferences (gear icon). If you want everything, "
"choose \"All\" and nothing is filtered."
msgstr ""
"You can switch anytime in Preferences (gear icon). If you want everything, "
"choose \"All\" and nothing is filtered."

